==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unprobably
<hw>Un*prob"a*bly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Un-</ets> + L.
<ets>probabilis</ets> approvable, fr. <ets>probare</ets> to approve. Cf.
<er>Probable</er>.]</ety> <def>In a manner not to be approved of;
improperly.</def> <mark>[Obs. & R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To diminish, by the authority of wise and knowing men, things
unjustly and <qex>unprobably</qex> crept in.</q>
<rj><qau>Strype.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unproficiency</ent>⟦br⟧
